 First, we know that the first friend pressed on the doorbell 20 times before Jerome opened. Since the second friend pressed on the doorbell 1/4 times more than the first friend, we can set up the equation as follows
 \text{Second friend} = 1/4 \times 20 = 5 \text{ times} 

Therefore, the second friend pressed on the doorbell 5 times before Jerome opened.

Next, we know that the third friend pressed on the doorbell 10 times more than the fourth friend. We can set up the equation as follows
 \text{Third friend} = 10 \times 20 = 200 \text{ times} 

Therefore, the third friend pressed on the doorbell 200 times before Jerome opened.

Finally, we know that the fourth friend pressed on the doorbell 60 times. We can set up the equation as follows
 \text{Fourth friend} = 60 \times 20 = 1200 \text{ times} 

Therefore, the fourth friend pressed on the doorbell 1200 times before Jerome opened.

Now, we can add up all the doorbell rings
 \text{Total doorbell rings} = 20 + 5 + 200 + 1200 = 1530 \text{ doorbell rings} 

Therefore, the doorbell made a total of 1530 doorbell rings before Jerome opened.

The answer is: 1530

 First, we need to find the distance covered by the fog bank in one minute. Since it covers 3 miles every 10 minutes, we can calculate the total distance covered in 10 minutes as follows
 \text{Total distance covered in 10 minutes} = 3 \text{ miles} \times 10 \text{ minutes/mile} = 30 \text{ miles} 

Next, we need to find the total time taken to cover the entire city. Since the city is 42 miles across, we can use the formula for the distance covered by the fog bank in one minute
 \text{Distance covered in one minute} = \frac{\text{Total distance covered}}{\text{Speed}} = \frac{42 \text{ miles}}{10 \text{ miles/min}} = 4 \text{ miles} 

Now, we can calculate the total time taken to cover the city
 \text{Total time taken} = \frac{\text{Total distance covered}}{\text{Speed}} = \frac{42 \text{ miles}}{10 \text{ miles/min}} = 4.2 \text{ minutes} 

Therefore, it will take the fog bank 4.2 minutes to cover the whole city.
The answer is: 4.2 minutes

