 Since Stanley's comb fell 4,000 feet, we can calculate the distance Oliver must climb to reach Stanley's comb. The distance from Stanley's position to the comb is 4,000 feet. Since Oliver is at a lower elevation, we can use the formula for the distance between two points on a flat surface, which is given by the Pythagorean theorem. The distance from Stanley's position to the comb is the square root of the sum of the squares of the distances from Stanley's position to each point. 

The distance from Stanley's position to the comb is \text{Distance} = \sqrt{(10,000)^2 + (4,000)^2} 
 \text{Distance} = \sqrt{100,000,000 + 16,000,000} 
 \text{Distance} = \sqrt{116,000,000} 
 \text{Distance} \approx 12,000 \text{ feet} 

